From ea35ada17ecbd832f1d54676ebeb476e2f7eb6cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 02:43:43 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] feat(agentic): add action-grounded inspection facts
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Sage's Eyes V2 — turns the field test's real observations into a versioned, deterministically
addressed observation set that downstream layers cite by ID, so a mission can be grounded in a
fact Sage actually saw rather than a phrase a model produced.

  - src/lib/launch/observed-facts.ts:
    · ObservedFactV1 — one atomic fact (control / visible text / state) with a deterministic
      sha256 id, source (dom | field_transition | vision), grounding (seen | inferred), decisive
      flag, page/state ids, exact visible texts, element role/name, source image index, confidence
      (only where model-derived), provenance digest.
    · ActionTransitionV1 — one safe action Sage performed and the state change it caused: safe verb,
      a robust role+name locator, before/after state digests, the visible-text delta, whether an
      observable change occurred, and field-test provenance.
    · deriveObservations() / deriveActionOutcomes() / decisiveFacts() / factIndex() /
      publicObservationView() — all pure + deterministic (no model, no browser, no network).

  Load-bearing rules (enforced deterministically, never by a model): ids/digests are sha256 over
  canonical content; DOM + field-test facts are `seen`; vision facts are `inferred` and NEVER
  decisive; any exact text vision emits must already appear in the captured source (invented text is
  dropped); duplicates canonicalize, the same text on a different page/state stays distinct.

  Attached to ProductMapV1.observations AFTER the map digest (like fieldTest/vision), so it is
  digest-neutral and rides in the existing untyped inspection_jobs.result JSON — additive, no DB
  migration, old artifacts still readable.

Tests (12): field-test transitions become seen facts; vision cannot invent text; inferred facts
can't be decisive; duplicates canonicalized while cross-state conflicts stay distinct; ids
deterministic; missing ids rejected; old/ran=false artifacts read cleanly; action→outcome ties an
action to its state change + facts; the public view leaks no observed text.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
