MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Make Sage visibly ACT, not only read. At inspection time (never payout, never a tester), Sage can
re-perform a safe action it already executed during the field test and verify the same observable
change still happens — a drift/robustness signal for mission design.

  - src/lib/launch/inspection-replay.ts:
    · InspectionProbeV1 — built ONLY from a real ActionTransitionV1 Sage executed + observed.
    · buildProbe() — deterministic safety gate (no browser): verb ∈ {click,press,scroll}; a robust
      role+name locator taken from the observed element (never model-authored); the expected change
      must be grounded in a `seen` after-state fact; rejects unsafe / state-changing / non-replayable
      / ungrounded transitions.
    · runInspectionProbe() — executes in a fresh ephemeral context through the C4 guarded egress
      proxy, bounded + cleaned up; a CLICK target must resolve to exactly one element. Classifies:
      reproduced | product_drift | locator_ambiguous | no_observable_change | probe_flake |
      infrastructure_failure. Emits honest replay_* events — a `replay_reproduced` is emitted ONLY
      after the browser actually performed the action and verified the change.
    · INSPECTION_REPLAY_MODE=off|shadow (default off); runReplayShadow() is a no-op unless shadow and
      never touches money or mission acceptance.

Tests: 8 deterministic gate cases (mode, grounded build, reject unsafe/state-changing/non-replayable/
no-locator/ungrounded); 7 real-browser cases on controlled local products (click→text reproduces,
press→state reproduces, ambiguous rejected, no-change honest, drift both ways, hung nav cleaned up) —
each proving the classification is earned and success is never claimed unverified.
`npm run test:inspection-replay` runs the browser suite.

