From 2107f43aea8a03ec7eb0c2708f877d54e8fca43b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 03:03:11 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] feat(agentic): ground missions in observed product facts
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Mission Brain V2 — a deterministic GROUNDING gate so a mission cannot compile unless every criterion
traces to something Sage actually observed, with capable evidence. A candidate may carry a design-time
grounding map (groundingV1) tying each criterion to observed-fact ids, the evidence requirement that
proves it, and a verification mode; the gate (pure, no model) rejects it when:

  · a cited fact/transition id does not exist in the inspection's observation set → ungrounded_fact_ref
  · a criterion's only sources are inferred (vision), not seen                     → inferred_decisive_source
  · a criterion has no grounding entry / a bad evidence index                      → criterion_evidence_unmapped
  · the verification mode cannot prove the criterion (url mode w/o a page source,
    observation mode w/o a state source)                                          → evidence_mode_incapable

  - src/lib/launch/mission-grounding.ts: validateMissionGrounding(), coverageReport() (inspected vs
    covered states, uncovered gaps, risk diversity, evidence-mode distribution, duplicate coverage),
    stripGrounding() (design-time metadata never reaches canonical compilation).
  - Wired into validateMission/validatePlanMissions as an OPTIONAL param threaded from map.observations —
    a candidate without groundingV1, or an inspection without an observation set, is a NO-OP, so the
    existing anchor gate and every current mission test are byte-identical (236 launch tests pass).
  - schemas.ts: additive VerificationMode, CriterionGroundingV1, MissionGroundingV1 (display-only, NOT in
    any spec digest, stripped at compile — like anchors); 4 new MissionValidationCodes; a structured
    CriticIssueCode vocabulary + optional MissionCritique.issueCodes.

Budget arithmetic and the canonical MissionSpec contracts are untouched. The live architect prompt is
NOT changed (that needs live re-validation, currently quota-blocked); the gate is ready to enforce
grounding as soon as the architect emits it — and the demo/tests exercise it with fixtures.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
