P-GEN metrics for Mission Brain V2 — deterministic quality measures over a round of candidates + their
validation reports, computed purely from what the gate found and the observation set (same inputs →
same numbers). computeGroundingMetrics() reports anchor integrity, fact-reference integrity,
criterion↔evidence mapping, target-scope validity, unsafe/auth count, invalid-reward/cap, duplicate
rate, the coverage report, and critic parse failures, plus a `promotionClean` flag that is true only
when every hard metric is perfect (integrities 100%, zero unsafe, zero parse failures).

Tests (7, offline): direct-report aggregation (clean round → promotionClean; ungrounded ref, unsafe
mission, scope violation, and critic parse failures each block promotion); and two END-TO-END through
the REAL gate — a grounded/in-scope/safe mission is accepted and scores clean, while a mission citing a
non-existent fact is rejected (ungrounded_fact_ref). Measures only; never changes the gate, the
architect, or budget arithmetic. The live architect round is quota-blocked; the resumable promotion
runner (Gate C) is the live path when quota clears.

