Subject: [PATCH 5/7] feat(concierge): add resumable autonomous task runs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Upgrades the concierge from a stateless chat/tool loop into a resumable, bounded TASK CONTROLLER —
the deterministic core that carries a founder's goal from intake to a live campaign and survives a
restart. It rides in the existing per-chat JSON storage (ConversationMemoryV2 reads a legacy bare
message array transparently), so no DB migration.

  - src/lib/telegram/task-run.ts:
    · TaskRunV1 — runId, goal, product url, budget (founder text + the tool-validated value), state,
      authoritative ids (inspection/plan/deployment/campaign), pending approval, retry counters,
      blockers, timestamps.
    · TaskState machine: intake → inspecting → waiting_for_inspection → presenting_plan →
      awaiting_approval → deploying → waiting_for_deployment → active → monitoring → completed/blocked.
    · advance() — PURE: given the current run + the latest deterministic tool outcome (or founder
      message), returns the updated run + the single next permitted action + honest events. Invariants:
      authoritative ids/state come ONLY from a successful tool result (a founder/model text can never
      set one); after a success it advances to the next step; a failed read-only tool retries with
      bounded backoff then blocks; a money tool is NEVER blindly retried — an ambiguous timeout triggers
      verify_deployment (re-spend only if verified NOT deployed); it STOPS at awaiting_approval; rounds
      are capped.
    · ConversationMemoryV2 (version, rolling messages, bounded summary, activeTask, recent tool
      outcomes) + readMemory() upgrading legacy storage and dropping an unknown task version.

Tests (8, fake tools, no LLM/network): Scenario A (intake→inspect→poll→stop at approval), B (resume
from storage→approve→fund→active→completed using saved ids), C (read-only failure→bounded→blocked, no
invented success), D (a text-claimed id can never become authoritative), E/E2 (ambiguous money timeout
→ verify not re-spend; re-attempt only if not deployed), a needsFunding failure blocks (no blind
retry), and the memory upgrade path.

The live runConcierge loop wiring is intentionally deferred (it needs live model testing, currently
quota-blocked); the controller is proven deterministically here and driven end-to-end in the P6 demo.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
