Observation Judge V2 — a SHADOW-ONLY lane that uses the Eyes-V2 seen facts + action transitions to
require ACTION→OUTCOME grounding, defeating a class the string corpus tolerates: generic action
language ("I clicked start") with no state-specific corroboration.

  - src/lib/deputy/observation-judge-v2.ts: judgeObservationV2() checks (deterministically, no LLM)
    that an account contains a mission-relevant action, at least one SPECIFIC observed-state token
    (distinctive corpus words + element names, token-matched so a genuine paraphrase still corroborates
    while a generic account does not), a coherent action→outcome pair, and no contradiction (a quoted
    UI control that was never observed). compareV2ToLegacy() categorizes agreement/disagreement.
  - OBS_JUDGE_V2_MODE=off|shadow (default off). Shadow runs, is compared to the legacy verdict, and the
    leak-safe view journals COUNTS + reason codes + digests only — never a matched string. It NEVER
    changes the money outcome; the frozen LLM judge is untouched.

Tests (14, deterministic): the 12 required fixtures — genuine detailed passes; genuine terse but
state-specific passes; GENERIC ACTION ("I clicked start") FAILS (the key win: action present, zero
specific state); generic guesser fails; correct-action/wrong-state fails; invented UI text →
contradiction fails; partial journey has no coherent pair; multilingual genuine → the deterministic
shadow can't corroborate an English corpus → reported as a v2_stricter disagreement (not a bug);
multilingual guesser fails; injection fails; a replay still grounds (dedup is the pipeline's job) —
plus mode gating and the text-free leak-safe view.

The pipeline wiring is gated behind OBS_JUDGE_V2_MODE (needs the observation set threaded from the
campaign) and is exercised in the P6 demo; the money lane is unchanged.

